Police on Monday pounced on suspects named in the ongoing National Youth Service probe after the DPP ordered their immediate prosecution. Thirteen of the suspects were arrested in Nairobi while four were nabbed in Naivasha. The NYS Director-General Richard Ndubai is among those who have been arrested. The suspects have been taken to DCI headquarters on Kiambu Road, Nairobi. Here is the list some of those arrested:   DPP Noordin Haji recommends immediate prosecution of all suspects named in NYS financial scandal.